cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CR

The paper discusses the analysis of multimedia content related to natural disasters, which includes text, visual content from social media, and satellite imagery. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) for the analysis of visual content and text, respectively. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning and deep learning techniques for disaster detection, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
